Rudyard Kipling himself Penned his most famous story, the jungle book, in this hotel! Outside the entrance you will find a cheeky monkey himself (in statue form) ready to greet you and you also find a frames letter from the author himself waiting for you.

This very hotel claims to be one of the oldest in London, opening its doors in the year 1837 and over the years has played host to royalty, Oscar winners, and iconic musicians. Iâve found myself thinking about the weight of things, recently. About how love feels so light when youâre holding it, but somehow heavy when itâs gone. About how some words are heavier than others, but they all weigh nothing until they leave your mouth.
ï»¿
ï»¿Iâve been thinking about the weight of these poems, too. With you they were light; easy. I swear I would wake up and find them littering your skin. Recently theyâve been heavy, and sharper than they used to be. I no longer find the words scattered amongst the light, I need to pull them like an anchor from my chest.
ï»¿
ï»¿Today, everything is heavier than it used to be. Everything is sharp enough to break the skin.
ï»¿
